    "plan_content": "Here's the implementation plan I've prepared:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `uv cache stats` Subcommand\n\n### Context\n`uv cache size` only prints a single total. The new `uv cache stats` subcommand iterates `CacheBucket::iter()`, computes per-bucket disk usage via `diskus`, and prints each bucket's size plus a final `total:` line — with optional `--human` formatting.\n\n### 4 Changes Required\n\n**1. `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`**\n- Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` enum (after `Size(SizeArgs)`)\n- Add `StatsArgs` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`) with `pub human: bool` and the same `#[arg(long = \"human\", short = 'H', alias = \"human-readable\")]` attribute\n\n**2. New file `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`**\n- Mirrors `cache_size.rs` in imports and structure — no preview guard\n- Loops over `CacheBucket::iter()`, calls `cache.bucket(bucket)` for the path, checks existence, runs `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()`\n- Prints `\"{bucket}: {size}\"` per bucket (using `CacheBucket`'s `Display` impl, e.g. `\"wheels-v6\"`)\n- Accumulates total, prints `\"total: {size}\"` at the end\n- Formats with `human_readable_bytes` when `human_readable` is `true`, otherwise raw `u64`\n\n**3. `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`**\n- Add `mod cache_stats;` alongside `mod cache_size;` (line 84)\n- Add `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` alongside the existing re-export (line 21)\n\n**4. `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`**\n- Add dispatch arm after `CacheCommand::Size`:\n  ```rust\n  Commands::Cache(CacheNamespace {\n      command: CacheCommand::Stats(args),\n  }) => commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer),\n  ```\n  (No `globals.preview` — no experimental guard needed)\n\n### Verification\n```bash\ncargo check -p uv                  # compile check\ncargo test -p uv cache             # integration tests\nuv cache stats                     # raw bytes output\nuv cache stats --human             # human-readable\nuv cache stats -H                  # short flag\nuv cache stats --human-readable    # alias\n```",
